DESCRIPTION:Building: Sophia Gordon Hall\nCity: Somerville\, MA 02144\nR
 oom: Sophia Gordon Hall - Multipurpose Room\nCampus: Medford/Somerville 
 campus\nWheelchair Accessible: Yes\nOpen to Public: Yes\nPrimary Audienc
 e: Alumni and Friends\,Faculty\,Interns and Residents\,Parents\,Postdoct
 oral Fellows\,Staff\,Students (Graduate)\,Students (Postdoctoral)\,Stude
 nts (Undergraduate)\nEvent Type: Performance\nEvent Subject: Theater/Dan
 ce\nEvent Sponsor: School of Arts and Sciences\nEvent Sponsor Department
  / Area: Theatre\, Dance\, and Performance Studies department\nEvent Spo
 nsor Details: Tufts Dance Program\nRSVP Information: dance@tufts.edu\nAd
 mission/Cost: Free and Open to the Public\nEvent Contact Name: Jaclyn Wa
 guespack\nEvent Contact Email: dance@tufts.edu\nEvent Contact Phone: 617
 -627-2556\n\nTufts Dance Program faculty member Ian Berg leads a tap wor
 kshop followed by an open tap jam with live musicians. Bring tap shoes o
 r sneakers for moving! Anyone at any level is welcome to join!\n\nClass
 \n6:15-7:00PM\n\nOpen Jam\n7:00-9:00PM\n\nSophia Gordon Multi-purpose Roo
 m\, 15 Talbot Avenue\, Medford\, MA 02155\n\nFree and open to all. No re
 gistration required. Free parking available.
