X-SOURCE-ID:emerson_theatres
X-SOURCE:Emerson Theatres
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T235959
DTSTAMP:20260313T222335
CREATED:20260311T143554Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260311T164104Z
UID:10000078-1775174400-1775260799@emersontheatres.org
SUMMARY:Orwell 2+2=5
DESCRIPTION:George Orwell was one of the most visionary authors of the 20th Century\, whose novels\, 1984 and Animal Farm\, foretold a chilling\, authoritarian future. Acclaimed director Raoul Peck (I Am Not Your Negro) interweaves clips\, readings from Orwell’s diary\, cinematic references\, and modern-day footage to craft not only a portrait of the writer\, but a fresh take on how prophetic his work has become.
URL:https://artsemerson.org/events/shared-stories-orwell/#new_tab
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://emersontheatres.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/81/2026/03/Orwell-with-AE-Logo.png
END:VEVENT
