DESCRIPTION:Building: Aidekman Arts Center\nCity: Medford\, MA 02155\nRo
 om: Balch Arena Theater\nCampus: Medford/Somerville campus\nOpen to Publ
 ic: Yes\nEvent Type: Performance\nEvent Subject: Theater/Dance\nEvent Sp
 onsor: School of Arts and Sciences\nEvent Contact Name: John Stark\nEven
 t Contact Email: John.Stark@tufts.edu\nLink: https://www.tuftstdpsticket
 s.com/section/tdps-2025-2026-season-ywz8\n\nTerayama Shuji’s 1975 play\,
  A Journal of the Plague Year\, pushes us to think about the violence of
  a nation’s imperial past (or present!) and epidemic disease both as a l
 iteral threat and as a metaphor for the way war crimes infect victims an
 d perpetrators alike.\n\nIt can also be seen as a play about protest\, r
 esistance\, and activism. Its emphasis on memory\, for instance\, as an 
 act of resistance against colonial amnesia\, and community in the face o
 f all that tears us apart\, is profoundly relevant for a 21st-century US
 -based audience. \n\nThe message of hopeful urgency at the end of the pl
 ay—“The time is now! The time is now!”—captures the spirit of student pr
 otest today.
CATEGORIES:Theatre, Dance, and Performance Studies
